    {
      "ID": 360910,
      "GUID": "F0A4984B-942D-4271-95F7-D635FD7D6735",
      "Title": "",
      "AgendaSequence": 0,
      "MinutesSequence": 1,
      "Version": "",
      "MinutesNote": "The Majority Leader (Council Member Cumbo) presiding as the Acting President Pro Tempore.",
      "LastModified": "2020-05-15T01:58:30.02Z"
    },
    {
      "ID": 360911,
      "GUID": "16B0F1D7-C4B0-485C-8282-E1F98A6B2103",
      "Title": "",
      "AgendaSequence": 0,
      "MinutesSequence": 3,
      "Version": "",
      "MinutesNote": "The presence of a quorum was announced by the Majority Leader and Acting President Pro Tempore (Council Member Cumbo).\r\n\r\nThere were 50 Council Members marked present at this Stated Meeting held remotely.\r\n\r\n\r\n     At the time of this Stated Meeting, there was one vacant seat on the Council in the 37th District (Brooklyn).",
      "LastModified": "2020-06-24T15:10:29.373Z"
    },
    {
      "ID": 360913,
      "GUID": "812DDB22-A187-4318-8329-D1BBC79236DD",
      "Title": "",
      "AgendaSequence": 0,
      "MinutesSequence": 6,
      "Version": "",
      "MinutesNote": "At this point, Council Member Koslowitz made a motion to suspend certain Rules of the Council pursuant to Rule 10.20 in relation to certain emergency measures made in response to the public health risk posed by the Coronavirus pandemic.    She noted that this suspension and amendment to the Rules of the Council would last only for the duration of the declared Coronavirus emergency by the Governor of New York State or the Mayor of New York City pursuant to New York Executive Law.  \r\n\r\nCouncil Member Koslowitz requested a suspension of the following Rules of the Council:\r\n2.30, 5.10, 6.00, 6.30, 7.50(b) and (c), 7.70(a), 7.130, 8.40(a), and 11.60(a).\r\n\r\nCouncil Member Koslowitz also declared that her motion would allow the Speaker to suspend any other Rule of the Council that would prevent he Council and its committees from conducting their regular business remotely, as long as that suspension is consistent with Federal, state and local law.  To make such additional suspensions, she noted, the Speaker would need to publish the rules being suspended on the Council website.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
      "LastModified": "2020-05-15T01:58:30.037Z"
    },
